<AddOnInstructionDefinitions Use="Context">
<EncodedData EncodedType="AddOnInstructionDefinition" Name="AOI_LadderSFC_Sequencer" Class="Standard" Revision="2.0" Vendor="ITG Inc." SignatureID="A8DB3222" SignatureTimestamp="2025-10-31T19:54:35.364Z" EditedDate="2025-10-31T19:54:35.364Z" SoftwareRevision="v37.01" EncryptionConfig="9">
<Description>
<![CDATA[Ladder Implementation of SFC - Sequence Manager block]]>
</Description>
<RevisionNote>
<![CDATA[Added pausability & String IO variable for StepName]]>
</RevisionNote>
<AdditionalHelpText>
<![CDATA[
This AOI, when paired with AOI_LadderSFC_Step & AOI_LadderSFC_StepMultiFork, is used for creating linear and basic forking sequences within ladder logic. This includes functionality such as Pausing, Resetting, Minimum Step Times, Delays, Watchdogs, Integer Steps, Bitmapped Steps, and some additional diagnostics.

For each sequencer, the AOI_LadderSFC_Sequencer should be at the top of the scan, followed by each step instruction. 

Steps automatically map out to an integer value within the ioStepData array, and will automatically remap if a step is added or removed. ]]>
</AdditionalHelpText>
